This is a bug in the SWT Tree control (win32). As soon as the first listener is registered for SWT.DefaultSelection, doubleclicks on the "+" or "-" don't work any more.

This can easily be reproduced in the Control Example by adding such a listener to the Tree control. With the SWT.DefaultSelection installed, doubleclicking on "+" only expands a tree item, but does *not* send out a DefaultSelection event.

Tree#wmNotifyChild(..):
		[..]
		case OS.NM_DBLCLK: {
			if (hooks (SWT.DefaultSelection)) return LRESULT.ONE;
			break;
		}
		[..]
=> Should not return LRESULT.ONE if the click target was the "+" / "-" box and not the item.

