The following line comes back null if there is no nature, which happens if the project is a java project.

IVirtualComponent vc = ComponentCore.createComponent(project);

This is overkill and is dangerous. 
The right way to do this according to Chuck Bridgham is to use the following:

    ResourcesPlugin.getWorkspace().getRoot().getProject(projectName)

which happens to be in a class called ProjectUtilities we own.
This returns an IProject
at this point we can see if it exists.  

    iproject.exists();

If you want to find out what type of project it is you can call a method Chuck pointed to in their J2EEProjectUtilities class. 

J2EEProjectUtilities.getJ2EEProjectType(Iproject)

So It might be a good excercise to clean this code up to do things the recommended way or kill it all together.

